ResolutionNotes: We classify Opalina as a pathogen based on the assumption that while not directly feeding on host tissue they are likely absorbing nutrients that would otherwise be available to the host. Further research may indicate that this is not the case and they are in fact true commensals.

NodeNotes: Sporozoites attach to the external surface of insects and are trophically transmitted
